name: Papuanus Crater
description:
--Fig13--
Papuanus Crater is a creature from Tassili, an exoplanet located 622 light years from earth, orbiting the star Hoggar.
On the fields of Tassili, we found enormous forests of Papuanus, sometimes reaching billions of individuals. Papuanus captures sunlight and turns into food just like plants, then its frog-like legs spread the fruits to the surrounding areas, which contain hundreds of seeds, making it possible to perpetuate the species.
The two heads of Papuanus each have a large brain, so they can communicate with all the other creatures on the planet through its roots, in order to keep the balance of the ecosystem.
